## Font loading

Three font families are loaded in `web/src/index.css`:

- **Inter** — via Google Fonts CDN (`@import` at top). Used for body text fallback.
- **Mariupol** — locally hosted in `web/public/fonts/`:
  - Regular (400): `Mariupol-Regular.woff2`
  - Medium (500): `Mariupol-Medium.woff2`
  - Bold (700): `Mariupol-Bold.woff2`
- **Mariupol Strong** — locally hosted in `web/public/fonts/`:
  - Regular (400): `mariupol_strong_w.woff2`

All locally-hosted fonts use `font-display: swap` to avoid invisible text during load. Headings using `var(--font-display)` resolve to "Mariupol Strong" first, falling back to "Mariupol", then Inter, then system-ui.

When adding new font files: place in `web/public/fonts/` and add a matching `@font-face` block in `web/src/index.css` BEFORE the `:root` block.

