## Figma MCP / Plugin API

Resolve variables with `getLocalVariableCollections()`, `getLocalVariables()`, follow `VARIABLE_ALIAS` by id. Map Figma path → CSS using tables above.

---

## Token approximation rule

When mapping Figma values to tokens, treat **colors** and **sizes** differently.

### Colors (and other perceptual tokens)

- Prefer the **closest existing** Alias or Mapped token.
- **Never** add raw hex/rgb in components to “match Figma exactly.”
- Small drift in Figma (e.g. `#1f1f1f` vs black) is usually accidental, not a deliberate second color — use the semantic token.
- Escalate to the designer only when the mismatch looks **intentional** (e.g. two clearly different roles in the same frame).

**Examples:**

| Figma | Use | Do not |
|-------|-----|--------|
| `#1f1f1f` body text | `--text-default` | New “softer black” or raw hex |
| `#e7e7e7` border | `--border-default` | `--bg-badge` (wrong role) |
| `#b0b0b0` muted | `--text-disabled` | Lighter one-off gray |

### Sizes, radii, border-widths

- These affect **pixel layout**; 8px vs 10px vs 12px are visibly different — do not “approximate” a smaller size token.
- If no token matches: **add** one in Figma + `figma-variables.tsv` + `npm run build:tokens`, then use it.
- Temporary gap only: use the nearest size **with a TODO** to add the correct token — not as a permanent substitute.

**Examples:**

| Figma | Use | Do not |
|-------|-----|--------|
| 10px icon | `--size-2xsmall` (new) | `--size-small` (8px) without TODO |
| 22px radius | `--radius-2xlarge` (20px) if acceptable, else new token | Raw `22px` in CSS |
| 36px nav height | `--size-2xlarge` | `--size-4xlarge` (44px) |

### Confirm with designer

Only when a color or size mismatch appears **deliberate** in context (two roles, spec annotation, or repeated exact value across components) — not for routine Figma export drift.

