## Approved exceptions

The design system uses CSS custom properties for all UI styling.
The following raw values are documented exceptions where no token
exists yet:

### Gradient effects (Button Special variant)

Located in `web/src/design-system/Button/Button.module.css`:

- `#fdd07f` — light amber start of linear-gradient on Special border,
  label, and icons. Pairs with `var(--accent-secondary)` (orange-500) end stop.
- `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.68)` — soft white center of radial-gradient
  on Special hover state. Pairs with `var(--accent-secondary)` edge.
- `#FDD07F` — same amber inside Button.tsx SVG `<linearGradient>`
  (for icon fills that need gradient tinting).

**Status:** TODO — add gradient tokens to design system (e.g.
`--gradient-special-linear`, `--gradient-special-hover-radial`,
`--brand-orange-200` if missing) when the next component needs gradient
effects. At that point, replace these raw values in Button.module.css
and Button.tsx.

**Rule for new components:** do not add new raw hex/rgba values. If
you find yourself wanting to add a gradient with raw values — STOP,
add the gradient token to Figma + build.mjs FIRST, then implement.

